🔹 LeetCode Problem 1045 – Customer Who Bought All Products
Problem:
 From the Customer table, find customers who bought all the products listed in the Product table.

💻 SQL Solution

SELECT customer_id
FROM Customer
GROUP BY customer_id
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT product_key) = 
 (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Product);

🔍 Explanation
GROUP BY customer_id → Groups purchases by each customer.
COUNT(DISTINCT product_key) → Counts unique products bought by that customer.
Subquery (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Product) → Total products available.
HAVING ensures we select only customers who bought all products.

